# DedgeAuth Ecosystem

## Current Environment

| Component | Server | Details |
|-----------|--------|---------|
| **App server (IIS)** | `dedge-server` | All apps as IIS virtual applications on port 80 (see deploy profiles) |
| **Database server** | `t-no1fkxtst-db` | PostgreSQL on port 8432, database `DedgeAuth` |
| **Credentials** | `postgres` / `postgres` | Connection string in `appsettings.json` |

This is the **test environment**. All apps are designed to be portable to any server (e.g. `p-no1fkxprd-app` for production) by changing only configuration -- never code. See "Server Portability" section below.

## Consumer Apps

DedgeAuth is the authentication and authorization server. Consumer apps depend on it, plus a static documentation site:

| App | Source Path | Repo Branch | Build Script | AppId | ApiPort |
|-----|------------|-------------|--------------|-------|---------|
| **DedgeAuth** | `C:\opt\src\DedgeAuth` | `main` | `.\Build-And-Publish.ps1` | — (server) | 8100 |
| **DocView** | `C:\opt\src\DocView` | `main` | `.\Build-And-Publish.ps1` | `DocView` | 8282 |
| **GenericLogHandler** | `C:\opt\src\GenericLogHandler` | `feature/auth-extraction` | `.\Build-And-Publish.ps1` | `GenericLogHandler` | 8110 |
| **ServerMonitorDashboard** | `C:\opt\src\ServerMonitor` | `feature/auth-extraction` | `.\Build-And-Publish.ps1` | `ServerMonitorDashboard` | 8998 |
| **AutoDocJson** | `C:\opt\src\AutoDocJson` | `main` | `.\Build-And-Publish.ps1` | `AutoDocJson` | 5280 |
