All repos are on Azure DevOps under `Dedge/Dedge`.

**Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1** (in DedgeAuth root) can rebuild DedgeAuth and all consumer apps that reference `DedgeAuth.Client` in one go. It scans `$env:OptPath\src` for `.csproj` files referencing DedgeAuth.Client, builds DedgeAuth first, then each consumer app sequentially.

## How Apps Connect

```
Browser
  |
  v
IIS (port 80, Default Web Site)
  |
  +-- /DedgeAuth                  --> DedgeAuth.Api (auth server, login UI, JWT tokens)
  +-- /DocView                 --> DocView (document viewer)
  +-- /GenericLogHandler       --> GenericLogHandler.WebApi (log aggregation)
  +-- /ServerMonitorDashboard  --> ServerMonitorDashboard (server monitoring)
  +-- /AutoDocJson             --> AutoDocJson (documentation tool)
  +-- /AgriNxt.GrainDryingDeduction --> AgriNxt.GrainDryingDeduction (grain drying deduction)
  +-- /AutoDoc                 --> AutoDoc (static documentation site)
```

- All apps run as **IIS virtual applications** under `Default Web Site` on `dedge-server`.
- Each app has its own **app pool** (same name as virtual path).
- IIS deployment is managed by the **IIS-DeployApp** system using `.deploy.json` profile templates (see "IIS-DeployApp" section below).
- Consumer apps reference `DedgeAuth.Client` (project reference) for auth middleware and proxy endpoints.
- DedgeAuth stores app registrations, user permissions, and tenant routing in PostgreSQL on `t-no1fkxtst-db:8432`.

## Authentication Flow (Auth Code Exchange)

1. User visits consumer app (e.g. `/GenericLogHandler/index.html`)
2. `DedgeAuthRedirectMiddleware` detects no token, redirects to `/DedgeAuth/login.html?returnUrl=...`
3. User logs in at DedgeAuth, gets JWT token + short-lived auth code
4. DedgeAuth redirects back to consumer app with `?code=<authCode>`
5. `DedgeAuthTokenExtractionMiddleware` exchanges code server-to-server via `POST /api/auth/exchange`
6. JWT stored in `DedgeAuth_access_token` cookie, browser redirected to clean URL
7. `DedgeAuthSessionValidationMiddleware` validates session via `GET /api/auth/validate` (cached 30s)
8. On cache miss, fires-and-forgets `POST /api/visits/record` for visit tracking
9. `DedgeAuth-user.js` reads token from cookie, fetches `/api/DedgeAuth/me` for user info, renders user menu
10. Subsequent API calls include `Authorization: Bearer <jwt>` header

## UI Asset Proxy

Consumer apps load DedgeAuth CSS/JS through a **local proxy** (no hardcoded server URLs):

```
HTML: <link href="api/DedgeAuth/ui/common.css">
  |
  v
DedgeAuth.Client proxy: GET /api/DedgeAuth/ui/common.css
  |
  v
DedgeAuth server: GET {AuthServerUrl}/api/ui/common.css (UIController)
  |
  v
Response cached 1 hour, served to browser
```

- HTML files use **relative paths** (`api/DedgeAuth/ui/...`, no leading `/`)
- The proxy is registered by `MapDedgeAuthProxy()` in `Program.cs`
- Only `appsettings.json` → `DedgeAuth:AuthServerUrl` needs to change per environment

Available proxy assets: `common.css`, `user.css`, `user.js`, `theme.js`, `i18n.js`, `i18n/{lang}.json`

## Tenant CSS Flow

1. `DedgeAuth-user.js` calls `/api/DedgeAuth/me` to get tenant domain
2. Fetches `{DedgeAuthUrl}/tenants/{domain}/theme.css` (TenantsController endpoint)
3. CSS is read from `tenants.css_overrides` column in database
4. Injected into `<style id="DedgeAuth-tenant-css"></style>` element on the page

## Database Relationships

PostgreSQL database `DedgeAuth` on `t-no1fkxtst-db:8432`:

| Table | Key Data | Relationship |
|-------|----------|--------------|
| `apps` | `app_id`, `base_url`, `available_roles_json` | One row per consumer app |
| `tenants` | `domain`, `app_routing_json`, `css_overrides`, `logo_data`, `icon_data` | Multi-app routing + branding |
| `users` | `email`, `global_access_level`, `tenant_id` | FK to tenants |
| `app_permissions` | `user_id`, `app_id`, `role` | User's role per app |
| `user_visits` | `user_id`, `app_id`, `path`, `ip_address`, `visited_at` | Visit tracking (from middleware) |

- `apps.base_url` = the app's full URL (e.g. `http://dedge-server/GenericLogHandler`)
- `tenants.app_routing_json` = JSON mapping AppId to URL for the user menu app switcher
- `DatabaseSeeder.cs` creates default apps and tenant; `MigrateLocalhostUrlsAsync()` fixes stale localhost URLs

## Server Portability

Apps are designed to work on **any server** without code changes:

| What changes per environment | Where configured |
|------------------------------|-----------------|
| DedgeAuth server URL | `appsettings.json` → `DedgeAuth:AuthServerUrl` |
| Database connection | `appsettings.json` → `ConnectionStrings:AuthDb` |
| App base URLs | `apps.base_url` in database (set by IIS-DeployApp from deploy template's DedgeAuth block) |
| Tenant app routing | `tenants.app_routing_json` in database (updated by seeder or admin UI) |
| Logo URL | `tenants.logo_url` in database |
| Publish destination | `.pubxml` → `PublishUrl` / `PublishDir` |
| DedgeSign script path | `.csproj` → `PostBuild` / `PostPublishSign` target |

**NEVER hardcode server hostnames** in C# code, HTML, or JavaScript. The only exception is build/deploy infrastructure (`.pubxml`, `Build-And-Publish.ps1`, `.csproj` DedgeSign paths).

