### IIS-DeployApp Deploy Profiles

Each app has a `.deploy.json` template in `IIS-DeployApp\templates\`. Profile naming: `<SiteName>_<InstallSource>.deploy.json`

| Profile | AppType | InstallSource | ApiPort | HealthEndpoint |
|---------|---------|---------------|---------|----------------|
| `DedgeAuth_WinApp` | AspNetCore | WinApp | 8100 | /health |
| `GenericLogHandler_WinApp` | AspNetCore | WinApp | 8110 | /health |
| `DocView_WinApp` | AspNetCore | WinApp | 8282 | (none) |
| `ServerMonitorDashboard_WinApp` | AspNetCore | WinApp | 8998 | /api/IsAlive |
| `AgriNxt.GrainDryingDeduction_WinApp` | AspNetCore | WinApp | 5123 | (none) |
| `AutoDocJson_WinApp` | AspNetCore | WinApp | 5280 | /health |
| `AutoDoc_None` | Static | None | — | (none) |
| `DefaultWebSite_None` | Static (root redirect) | None | — | (none) |

Deploy steps: Teardown → Install files (WinApp/PshApp/None) → Create app pool → Create virtual app → web.config → Permissions → Start → Health check verify

